article.headline: Canisius 75, Youngstown State 68
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) -- Kevin Downey scored 27 points to lead Canisius over Youngstown State 75-68. Downey, who topped 1,500 career points Saturday, made a layup and free throw with 31 seconds left. That sealed the win after Youngstown's Keston Roberts brought the Penguins to within 70-68. Roberts led Youngstown State (7-18) with 19 points. Derrick Harris had 10 points and 12 assists and Quin Humphrey scored 10. The Penguins, who lost their sixth straight game, opened with a 13-0 run. Canisius responded with 12 straight points, but the Griffs went 0-10 from the 3-point arc in the first half, and Youngstown State led 33-25 at the break. Darnell Wilson led Canisius on a 14-5 spurt to open the second half. He finished with 17 points, and Joe Young added 13 for the Griffs (7-18).
